 ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert John Burnell was born in 1422, in Balgriffin, County Dublin, Ireland. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Robert Burnell. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"1422–":"1422–Surnud","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1450–1530":"1450–1530","1422–Male":"1422–Surnud","1425":"1425","1422":"1422","1530":"1530","5 May 1450":"5. mai 1450","1450":"1450","Balgriffin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Balgriffin, County Dublin, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1422–":"1422–Kuollut","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1450–1530":"1450–1530","1422–Male":"1422–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1422":"1422","1530":"1530","5 May 1450":"5. toukokuuta 1450","1450":"1450","Balgriffin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Balgriffin, County Dublin, Irlanti"},"fr":{"1422–":"1422–Décédé","1425–Female":"1425–Décédée","1450–1530":"1450–1530","1422–Male":"1422–Décédé","1425":"1425","1422":"1422","1530":"1530","5 May 1450":"5 mai 1450","1450":"1450","Balgriffin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Balgriffin, County Dublin, Irlande","lifeSummary":"Robert John Burnell est né en 1422, à Balgriffin, County Dublin, Irlande. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs. Robert Burnell. Il est décédé dans s